Title: DALEGO Composite Applications Application Agent, Java program  Course Project  
Author: Amy Junhong Long Instructor: Ben Zorn 
Date: 5535 Fall 1996  
Pubnum: CSCI  
Abstract: A large number of software applications have been developed in the past, most with single task capabilities. These applications now have demands on them however, which are more complex, or have more functionalities than they can provide for. Compositing existing applications into one powerful and convenient application is a solution. Placing an agent in charge of an existing application, and a manager in charge of all the agents, is a good structure of compositing. Interapplication communication is the key to this structure. A uniform interface between the manager and it's agents, and a standard interface between an agent and it's client application, is also necessary. A portable programming language is preferred to develop the manager and it's agents. An evaluation of Java concludes that it is a feasible language to program a composite application for writing an html file. But due to the lack of effective means of interapplication communications, Java may become very difficult to build a composite application for other purposes. 
